[{"id":"/sicpjs/5.2","tag":"TITLE","body":"5.2  A Register-Machine Simulator"},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p1","child":[{"body":"\n    In order to gain a good understanding of the design of register machines,\n    we must test the machines we design to see if they perform as expected.\n    One way to test a design is to hand-simulate the operation of the\n    controller, as in exercise ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"5.5","href":"/sicpjs/5.1.4#ex-5.5"},{"body":".  But this is\n    extremely tedious for all but the simplest machines.  In this section we\n    construct a simulator for machines described in the register-machine\n    language.  The simulator is a\n    JavaScript\n    program with\n    four interface\n    functions.\n    The first uses a description of a register\n    machine to construct a model of the machine (a data structure whose\n    parts correspond to the parts of the machine to be simulated), and the\n    other three allow us to simulate the machine by manipulating the\n    model:\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"UL","child":[{"tag":"LI","child":[{"tag":"JAVASCRIPTINLINE","body":"make_machine("},{"tag":"META","body":"register-names"},{"tag":"JAVASCRIPTINLINE","body":", "},{"tag":"META","body":"operations"},{"tag":"JAVASCRIPTINLINE","body":", "},{"tag":"META","body":"controller"},{"tag":"JAVASCRIPTINLINE","body":")"},{"tag":"BR"},{"body":"\n\tconstructs and returns a model of the machine with the given\n\tregisters, operations, and controller.\n      ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"LI","child":[{"tag":"JAVASCRIPTINLINE","body":"set_register_contents("},{"tag":"META","body":"machine-model"},{"tag":"JAVASCRIPTINLINE","body":", "},{"tag":"META","body":"register-name"},{"tag":"JAVASCRIPTINLINE","body":", "},{"tag":"META","body":"value"},{"tag":"JAVASCRIPTINLINE","body":")"},{"tag":"BR"},{"body":"\n\tstores a value in a simulated register in the given machine.\n      ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"LI","child":[{"tag":"JAVASCRIPTINLINE","body":"get_register_contents("},{"tag":"META","body":"machine-model"},{"tag":"JAVASCRIPTINLINE","body":", "},{"tag":"META","body":"register-name"},{"tag":"JAVASCRIPTINLINE","body":")"},{"tag":"BR"},{"body":"\n\treturns the contents of a simulated register in the given machine.\n      ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"LI","child":[{"tag":"JAVASCRIPTINLINE","body":"start("},{"tag":"META","body":"machine-model"},{"tag":"JAVASCRIPTINLINE","body":")"},{"tag":"BR"},{"body":"\n\tsimulates the execution of the given machine, starting from the\n\tbeginning of the controller sequence and stopping when it reaches the\n\tend of the sequence.\n      ","tag":"#text"}]}]}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p2","child":[{"body":"\n    As an example of how these\n    functions\n    are used, we can define\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"JAVASCRIPTINLINE","body":"gcd_machine"},{"body":"\n    to be a model of the GCD machine\n    of section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"5.1.1","href":"/sicpjs/5.1.1"},{"body":" as follows:\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":1,"eval":true,"prependLength":458,"program":"chap=4&-KC8LJT8rR1dMmZEKqESgAdxou36g1AAFpoUsVvQOmV6PYns8dAAuUApdJ8UhCchlPj3FT5TzeEpQirVWpMMpCdr0In0xllTgyFlM5zKEbHcZDUjTWYLeGrdacsrc6SgCWHNFsRIGM6cC6EK43SR3WaPdGvd4sT78CVS-6Xa63GUMpkwuHLTiI9rI1G645Y-GE4na9xFHylUDCKr0eqNATkChTIP0AAedWufGjwRkRnEkg5VrZvJ05FwoEyKv53CEhGYCfjMdJGjRfImguIIoL+OLTATTHu+FMCbJLoVpz4anmAD5QMQjjoPO82fQzjm83T082Y2XghXNC6G2cBZwRdSanUJXxZWnWQu9+ml6TR+ie0q+wsh1lOJfChP7dPc+drNxeCfz5n0euWBFSxWHYGxeEEEQU2lT9bBPEDaF-J9jmvGhb0HOhGCYfkeGLThHHyUA0XHJlX1XXUPi+JdTUIIFQRoBM2BWGIAhCKdYVFB0nS7MdyWKXxmIDIMIX2ag4LjBMk0gkwjxIno+hEoY-2HGsdmCbdKl3YMmj4YTBjg3pzzkvZBjlasBSWHwt0WYRgnjO9-SEQMtNDcNIxjZtcHjSTjFTS1WWGKQqxdYLdJifT5LVPDO247QUNzfshyEYJgjKQImAkVUrhYVKJHkAArIQZk4YhGmCUg+CC4L0V6STbJzdDPJUGQhEsi9eN9KE7XIWhCEcUCvxYE1QFWfRiFUStkL0JUyhscwup6swZBg79FGUGQRpYMayS8DrmPmwh4KlPh9vSgUckGJS4pxDJ3SJE6snOmI2p2yk9qYnrW1mdsf3us6ogujRCMmxVklSG6CSJW7jveg6Hv+p7nopfj-EEpgTrjLJvKgmS2SMyEDhkYJiCU9d8RYSwgMw5b+GTaTRW6g6nFWsI